---
// src/pages/about.astro
// About page introducing the site and its creators

import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Us – FunWithKidsBoston"
  description="Learn about FunWithKidsBoston — a family guide written by local Boston parents sharing the best things to do with kids in the Greater Boston area."
>
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 mb-6">About FunWithKidsBoston 🎉</h1>

    <div class="prose max-w-none">
      <p>
        Welcome! We're a local Boston family who loves exploring everything the Greater Boston area has to offer — from world-class museums and hidden parks to the best rainy-day indoor play spaces and road trips through beautiful New England.
      </p>

      <h2>Why We Started This Site</h2>
      <p>
        When we became parents, we found ourselves constantly searching for age-appropriate, family-friendly activities in the Boston area. While there's no shortage of things to do, finding reliable, up-to-date information from people who've actually been there with kids was surprisingly hard. So we decided to create the resource we wished we'd had.
      </p>

      <h2>What You'll Find Here</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>FunWithKidsBoston</strong> is your go-to guide for:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Things To Do</strong> — Museums, parks, playgrounds, zoos, and local attractions reviewed with families in mind.</li>
        <li><strong>Day Trips</strong> — Weekend adventures and easy road trips within a few hours of Boston.</li>
        <li><strong>Gear & Reviews</strong> — Honest reviews of family gear we actually use: strollers, rain gear, travel essentials, and more.</li>
        <li><strong>Seasonal Guides</strong> — The best activities for every season, from fall apple picking to summer beach trips.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Our Philosophy</h2>
      <p>
        We believe that every family outing doesn't have to be expensive or perfectly planned. Some of our best adventures have been spontaneous trips to a local playground or a simple walk along the Charles River. We aim to share practical, real-world tips that help families spend more quality time together — no matter your budget.
      </p>

      <h2>Affiliate Disclosure</h2>
      <p>
        Some of our articles contain affiliate links. This means we may earn a small commission if you click through and make a purchase, at no additional cost to you. We only recommend products and services we genuinely use and love. For full details, please see our <a href="/disclosure/">Affiliate Disclosure page</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
      <p>
        Have a question, suggestion, or want to share your own favorite Boston family spot? We'd love to hear from you! Drop us an email at <strong>hello@funwithkidsboston.com</strong>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>